.TH MVM 1 "May 2026" "mvmctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mvm \- MicroVM Manager - Container speed, VM isolation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mvm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mvm
is a production-grade CLI for managing microVMs on Linux.
It handles the full VM lifecycle: downloading kernels and images, setting up bridge networking,
creating and destroying VMs, SSH access, log streaming, snapshots, and cleanup.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with detailed error messages and stack traces.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show this help message and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS VM Management
.TP
.BR vm\ create
Create and start a new Firecracker VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ rm
Stop and remove VMs by short ID or name.
.TP
.BR vm\ ls
List running and stopped VMs.
.TP
.BR vm\ ps
List running VMs (alias for ls).
.TP
.BR vm\ snapshot
Snapshot VM memory and disk state.
.TP
.BR vm\ load
Load VM from snapshot.
.TP
.BR vm\ inspect
Show detailed information about a VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ start
Start the specified stopped VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ stop
Stop the specified running VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ pause
Pause the specified running VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ resume
Resume the specified paused VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ reboot
Reboot the specified VM.
.TP
.BR vm\ import
Create a VM from a portable config file.
.TP
.BR vm\ export
Export a VM's configuration to portable JSON.
.SS Host Configuration
.TP
.BR host\ init
Apply host configuration (KVM, modules, ip_forward, mvm group, sudoers).
.TP
.BR host\ ls
Show current host configuration state.
.TP
.BR host\ clean
Remove networking config (bridges, TAPs, iptables).
.TP
.BR host\ reset
Full rollback: networking + sysctl + sudoers + group removal.
.SS Kernel Management
.TP
.BR kernel\ ls
List cached kernels.
.TP
.BR kernel\ fetch
Download or build a kernel (official or Firecracker-optimized).
.TP
.BR kernel\ set-default
Set a kernel as the default for VM creation.
.TP
.BR kernel\ rm
Remove a cached kernel.
.SS Image Management
.TP
.BR image\ ls
List available and cached images.
.TP
.BR image\ fetch
Download an image by its ID (e.g., ubuntu-24.04, archlinux).
.TP
.BR image\ import
Import a local image file.
.TP
.BR image\ set-default
Set the default image for VM creation.
.TP
.BR image\ rm
Remove a cached image.
.TP
.BR image\ inspect
Show detailed image information.
.TP
.BR image\ warm
Pre-decompress image to ready pool.
.SS Binary Management
.TP
.BR bin\ ls
List local Firecracker versions.
.TP
.BR bin\ fetch
Download a specific Firecracker release.
.TP
.BR bin\ default
Set the active Firecracker version.
.TP
.BR bin\ rm
Remove a cached version.
.SS Network Management
.TP
.BR network\ create
Create a named bridge network.
.TP
.BR network\ rm
Remove a named network.
.TP
.BR network\ ls
List all networks.
.TP
.BR network\ inspect
Show network details and IP leases.
.TP
.BR network\ set-default
Set a network as the default for VM creation.
.TP
.BR network\ sync
Sync iptables rules between database and host.
.SS SSH Key Management
.TP
.BR key\ ls
List cached keys.
.TP
.BR key\ add
Import an existing public key.
.TP
.BR key\ create
Generate a new ED25519 keypair.
.TP
.BR key\ rm
Remove a key from the cache.
.TP
.BR key\ set-default
Set one or more keys as defaults for new VMs.
.TP
.BR key\ inspect
Show detailed information about a key.
.TP
.BR key\ export
Export a key to ~/.ssh or a custom directory.
.SS Cache Management
.TP
.BR cache\ init
Initialize cache directories.
.TP
.BR cache\ prune
Prune stale cache entries (VMs, networks, images, kernels).
.TP
.BR cache\ clean
Completely clean all cache — prune everything, host clean, remove cache dir.
.SS Other Commands
.TP
.BR console
VM console access (PTY-over-vsock relay).
.RS
.PP
.B \-\-state
Show console connection state and exit.
.PP
.B \-\-kill
Kill any existing console connection to the VM.
.RE
.TP
.BR config
Configuration management (get, set, list, reset).
.TP
.BR init
Initialize mvm (guided setup wizard).
.TP
.BR ssh
VM SSH access.
.TP
.BR logs
VM log management.
.RS
.PP
.B \-\-os
Show logs from the guest OS (serial console) instead of Firecracker.
.PP
.B \-\-follow
Follow log output in real-time (tail -f style).
.RE
.TP
.BR version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BR help
Show help for mvm or a subcommand.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.BR MVM_CACHE_DIR
Override cache directory (default: ~/.cache/mvmctl).
.TP
.BR MVM_CONFIG_DIR
Override config directory (default: ~/.config/mvmctl).
.TP
.BR MVM_FIRECRACKER_BIN
Override Firecracker binary path.
.TP
.BR MVM_LOG_LEVEL
Set log level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.cache/mvmctl/
Cache directory for binaries, kernels, images, VM state.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mvmctl/config.json
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/mvmctl/metadata.json
Asset registry (images, kernels, binaries with default flags).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
One-time host setup:
.RS
.nf
$ sudo mvm host init
# Log out and back in, or run: newgrp mvm
.fi
.RE
.PP
Download kernel and image:
.RS
.nf
$ mvm kernel fetch
$ mvm image fetch ubuntu-24.04
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create and start a VM:
.RS
.nf
$ mvm vm create --name myvm --image ubuntu-24.04
$ mvm logs myvm --follow
$ mvm ssh --name myvm
.fi
.RE
.PP
List and remove VMs:
.RS
.nf
$ mvm vm ls
$ mvm vm rm --name myvm --force
.fi
.RE
.PP
Network management:
.RS
.nf
$ mvm network create mynet --subnet 10.1.0.0/16
$ mvm vm create --name myvm2 --image ubuntu-24.04 --network mynet
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run interactive setup wizard:
.RS
.nf
$ mvm init
.fi
.RE
.SH PREREQUISITES
.IP \(bu 2
Linux (x86_64 or aarch64) - Firecracker only runs on Linux
.IP \(bu 2
KVM access (/dev/kvm) - add user to kvm group
.IP \(bu 2
Python 3.13+
.IP \(bu 2
System packages: iproute2, iptables, cloud-localds (cloud-image-utils on Debian/Ubuntu, cloud-utils on Arch), qemu-utils
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
After \fBsudo mvm host init\fR, normal mvm commands require no sudo.
.IP \(bu 2
Cache is stored at ~/.cache/mvmctl/ by default.
.IP \(bu 2
All assets are keyed by SHA256 hash (64 characters).
.IP \(bu 2
CLI displays only first 6 characters of hashes as short IDs.
